==Ladder==
All teams played 22 games during the home and away season, for a total of 176. An additional 9 games were played during the finals series.
{{AFL Ladder/1998}}
==Awards== *The [[Brownlow Medal]] was awarded to [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]] of {{AFL StK}} *The [[Leigh Matthews Trophy]] was awarded to [[Wayne Carey]] of {{AFL Nor}} *The [[Coleman Medal]] was awarded to [[Tony Lockett]] of {{AFL Syd}} *The [[Norm Smith Medal]] was awarded to [[Andrew McLeod]] of {{AFL Ade}} *The [[AFL Rising Star award]] was awarded to [[Byron Pickett]] of {{AFL Nor}} *The [[Wooden Spoon (award)|Wooden Spoon]] was "awarded" to {{AFL BL}}
==Notes== *{{AFL Ade}} became the first, and to date only, club since the introduction of the final five to win the premiership from outside the top four. The club was fifth at the end of the home-and-away season.<!-- Melbourne won the premiership from sixth in 1900 under a significantly different finals system -->
